My
room
was
a
charming
one.
He
implored
me
to
tell
him
anything
which
could
add
to
my
happiness.
It
was
on
the
tip
of
my
tongue
to
inform
him
that
a
blank
cheque
would
materially
help
towards
that
end,
but
I
felt
that
it
might
be
premature
in
the
present
state
of
our
acquaintance.
The
dinner
was
excellent,
and
as
we
sat
together
afterwards
over
his
Havanas
and
coffee,
which
later
he
